The paper discusses the design of neural hardware for cognitive systems, which falls under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE). The use of optical signals and superconducting detectors for energy efficiency and single-photon detection respectively suggests a focus on electronics and photonics (cs.ET, cs.OC). The discussion of spatial and temporal information integration and cognitive processing suggests a focus on artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI) and possibly also on pattern recognition and signal processing (cs.LG).
